A clash erupted in Dera Bugti when armed men from the Bugti tribe attacked a convoy of soldiers.
Gunbattles continued throughout the day, with tribesmen using light and heavy weapons.
The rebels seek autonomy and benefits from natural resources.
The violence escalated after a doctor's rape near the Sui gasfield.
Thousands fled as clashes left casualties.
The army deployed troops, and tensions rose as tribesmen surrounded government officials.
The situation remains volatile, with fears of renewed fighting.
The rebels demand more revenues and resent the army's presence in Baluchistan.
Violence has taken a toll on civilians, with casualties reported.
